        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(telegram): restore readable default text sends",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\nFixes #93263 by restoring Telegram's default text delivery, edits, and draft previews to the legacy-readable `sendMessage` / `editMessageText` path instead of the rich raw Bot API path.\r\n\r\nThis keeps the change scoped to the outage path:\r\n- default text sends now render HTML and fall back to plain text when Telegram rejects formatting\r\n- draft previews now use normal text send/edit calls again\r\n- Telegram default text chunk limits are pulled back to the standard text-message range instead of the rich-message limit\r\n- media delivery, buttons, quote handling, and related transport behavior stay in place\r\n\r\n## Why this shape\r\n\r\nIssue #93263 and the comment thread point to a Telegram outbound transport regression introduced with the rich-message rollout. The immediate goal here is to restore a readable default for all Telegram-bound agents before revisiting richer transport behavior.\r\n\r\n## Verification\r\n\r\nPassed:\r\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/telegram/src/draft-stream.test.ts`\r\n\r\nIn progress:\r\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/telegram/src/send.test.ts`\r\n  - currently narrowed to 11 remaining expectation migrations in tests after switching the default text path away from `sendRichMessage`\r\n\r\nNot yet run in this draft:\r\n- broader Telegram delivery tests\r\n- live Telegram client proof\r\n- autoreview (intentionally skipped for this draft-first pass per request)\r\n",
